#: src/3614-project-goals.md:9
msgid ""
"This RFC proposes to run an experimental goal program during the second half "
"of 2024 with nikomatsakis as owner/organizer. This program is a first step "
"towards an ongoing Rust roadmap. The proposed outcomes for 2024 are (1) "
"select an initial slate of goals using an experimental process; (2) track "
"progress over the year; (3) drawing on the lessons from that, prepare a "
"second slate of goals for 2025 H1. This second slate is expected to include "
"a goal for authoring an RFC proposing a permanent process."
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:11
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:14
msgid ""
"The Rust project last published an annual roadmap in 2021. Even before that, "
"maintaining and running the roadmap process had proved logistically "
"challenging. And yet there are a number of challenges that the project faces "
"for which having an established roadmap, along with a clarified ownership "
"for particular tasks, would be useful:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:16
msgid "Focusing effort and avoiding burnout:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:17
msgid ""
"One common contributor to burnout is a sense of lack of agency. People have "
"things they would like to get done, but they feel stymied by debate with no "
"clear resolution; feel it is unclear who is empowered to \"make the call\"; "
"and feel unclear whether their work is a priority."
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:18
msgid ""
"**Having a defined set of goals, each with clear ownership, will address "
"that uncertainty.**"
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:19
msgid "Helping direct incoming contribution:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:20
msgid ""
"Many would-be contributors are interested in helping, but don't know what "
"help is wanted/needed. Many others may wish to know how to join in on a "
"particular project."
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:21
msgid ""
"**Identifying the goals that are being worked on, along with owners for "
"them, will help both groups get clarity.**"
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:22
msgid "Helping the Foundation and Project to communicate"
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:23
msgid ""
"One challenge for the Rust Foundation has been the lack of clarity around "
"project goals. Programs like fellowships, project grants, etc. have "
"struggled to identify what kind of work would be useful in advancing project "
"direction."
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:24
msgid ""
"**Declaring goals, and especially goals that are desired but lack owners to "
"drive them, can be very helpful here.**"
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:25
msgid "Helping people to get paid for working on Rust"
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:26
msgid ""
"A challenge for people who are looking to work on Rust as part of their job "
"-- whether that be full-time work, part-time work, or contracting -- is that "
"the employer would like to have some confidence that the work will make "
"progress. Too often, people find that they open RFCs or PRs which do not "
"receive review, or which are misaligned with project priorities. A secondary "
"problem is that there can be a perceived conflict-of-interest because "
"people's job performance will be judged on their ability to finish a task, "
"such as stabilizing a language feature, which can lead them to pressure "
"project teams to make progress."
msgstr ""

#: src/3614-project-goals.md:27
msgid ""
"**Having the project agree before-hand that it is a priority to make "
"progress in an area and in particular to aim for achieving particular goals "
"by particular dates will align the incentives and make it easier for people "
"to make commitments to would-be employers.**"
msgstr ""

